 infrastructure, you know usually you have a server or infrastructure and you just make some changes with your infrastructure again and again over years.<\/p>\n<p>This is the main problem that how we are going to replicate this server with all those changes?<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/?attachment_id=10226\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-10226\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-10226\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Challenges-With-Traditional-Infrastructure-1024x571.png\" alt=\"Challenges With Traditional Infrastructure\" width=\"760\" height=\"424\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Challenges-With-Traditional-Infrastructure-1024x571.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Challenges-With-Traditional-Infrastructure-300x167.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Challenges-With-Traditional-Infrastructure-768x428.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Challenges-With-Traditional-Infrastructure.png 1195w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>To replicate traditional infrastructure, the teams bring a lot of documents or a very huge document which explain what the process for the replication for that environment, we usually go through all the process and create the environment but it&#8217;s not working because it is not the same, there is something is configured on the actual environment, but it is not known.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc65347799\"><\/a>Vicious circle of manual process<\/h2>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/?attachment_id=10235\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-10235\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-10235\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Vicious-Circle-of-manaual-process-1024x571.png\" alt=\"Vicious Circle of manaual process\" width=\"760\" height=\"424\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Vicious-Circle-of-manaual-process-1024x571.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Vicious-Circle-of-manaual-process-300x167.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Vicious-Circle-of-manaual-process-768x428.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Vicious-Circle-of-manaual-process.png 1192w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>This leads to a vicious circle of manual processes. So, let&#8217;s understand how this happened?<\/p>\n<p>For example, if we look at the manual process it is usually well documented, so you can understand exactly what the steps are and then you start it starts taking a long time to implement this documentation, and then at the end, it has errors which make you add more verification in the document and the process which increase the process which ends up with more documentation taking more time more errors add verification, and this is what happened<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc65347800\"><\/a>Infrastructure workflow<\/h2>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p>This is a general workflow, so it starts with source control. So, you put all your infrastructure as code in the source control and once you want to make any changes, you just get the latest and just make the change, once you complete the change, you don&#8217;t usually run the update or create or provision the infrastructure from your local machine, instead, the best practices usually is to push these changes to the remote repo and then run an automated build which will get the latest and start either creating or updating the environment.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/?attachment_id=10228\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-10228\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-10228\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Infrastructure-as-code-workflow-with-terraform-1024x572.png\" alt=\"Infrastructure as code workflow with terraform\" width=\"760\" height=\"425\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Infrastructure-as-code-workflow-with-terraform-1024x572.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Infrastructure-as-code-workflow-with-terraform-300x168.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Infrastructure-as-code-workflow-with-terraform-768x429.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Infrastructure-as-code-workflow-with-terraform.png 1195w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc65347801\"><\/a>Take-aways information<\/h2>\n<p><strong>Terraform Configuration file<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>You describe all the components or your entire datacentre or environment in terraform configuration file which has .tf extension.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><strong>Resource Graph<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Terraform builds a graph of all your resources and parallelizes the creation and modification of any non-dependent resources. because of this, Terraform builds infrastructure as efficiently as possible, and operators get insight into dependencies in their infrastructure.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><strong>Providers<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Terraform relies on plugins called &#8220;providers&#8221; to interact with remote systems. Terraform configurations must declare which providers they require so that Terraform can install and use them. Each provider adds a set of resource types and\/or data sources that Terraform can manage.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/?attachment_id=10234\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-10234\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-10234\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Terrafrom-configuration-file-terraform-resouce-graph-terraform-pluging-and-providers-1024x579.png\" alt=\"Terrafrom configuration file terraform resouce graph terraform pluging and providers\" width=\"760\" height=\"430\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Terrafrom-configuration-file-terraform-resouce-graph-terraform-pluging-and-providers-1024x579.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Terrafrom-configuration-file-terraform-resouce-graph-terraform-pluging-and-providers-300x170.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Terrafrom-configuration-file-terraform-resouce-graph-terraform-pluging-and-providers-768x435.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Terrafrom-configuration-file-terraform-resouce-graph-terraform-pluging-and-providers.png 1191w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><strong>Configure a Provider<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>provider &#8220;azurerm&#8221; { features { }<\/p>\n<p>version = &#8220;&gt;= 2.26\u201c } provider_x_y \u00e0 e.x. (azurerm_resource_group)<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><strong>Control terraform version or other behaviours<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>terraform { #&#8230; }<\/p>\n<p>Constrain a provider version<\/p>\n<p>terraform { required_providers { azurerm = { source = &#8220;hashicorp\/azurerm&#8221; version = &#8220;&gt;= 2.26&#8221; } } }<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2021\/02\/27\/terraform-associate-exam-guide-and-preparation\/terraform-provider-control-terraform-block-azurerm\/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-10233\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-10233\" src=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Terraform-provider-control-terraform-block-azurerm-1024x576.png\" alt=\"Terraform provider control terraform block azurerm\" width=\"760\" height=\"428\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Terraform-provider-control-terraform-block-azurerm-1024x576.png 1024w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Terraform-provider-control-terraform-block-azurerm-300x169.png 300w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Terraform-provider-control-terraform-block-azurerm-768x432.png 768w, https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/02\/Terraform-provider-control-terraform-block-azurerm.png 1195w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc65347802\"><\/a>Continue in the video\u2026\u2026<\/h2>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Terraform Associate Exam Guide and Preparation Agenda.\u00a0 Exam Objectives GitHub &hellip;<\/p>\n<p class=\"read-more\"> <a class=\"ast-button\" href=\"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/2021\/02\/27\/terraform-associate-exam-guide-and-preparation\/\"> <span class=\"screen-reader-text\">Terraform Associate Exam Guide and Preparation<\/span> Read More<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":10238,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"site-sidebar-layout":"default","site-content-layout":"default","ast-global-header-display":"","ast-banner-title-visibility":"","ast-main-header-display":"","ast-hfb-above-header-display":"","ast-hfb-below-header-display":"","ast-hfb-mobile-header-display":"","site-post-title":"","ast-breadcrumbs-content":"","ast-featured-img":"","footer-sml-layout":"","theme-transparent-header-meta":"","adv-header-id-meta":"","stick-header-meta":"","header-above-stick-meta":"","header-main-stick-meta":"","header-below-stick-meta":"","footnotes":""},"categories":[1],"tags":[1061,995,1023,1062,1064,1063],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/10224"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/mohamedradwan.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/moh